JOHANNESBURG - The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa has released CCTV footage of the recent train fires at Cape Town Station. READ: Shops looted at Joburg's Park Station, Prasa increasing security In it, two of the men wanted in connection with Thursday's attacks are clearly visible. The arson caused an estimated R60-million in property damage and destroyed 18 train carriages. The incident inconvenienced thousands of commuters. Prasa has offered R100,000 reward for information on the suspected arsonists. Metrorail and special investigators are working with police to find several people of interest.